Kvantni generator random števil¶

Ta Jupyter zvezek implementira kvantni generator random števil z uporabo Qiskita.

Predpogoji¶

  • Namestite potrebne pakete: qiskit, qiskit-aer, numpy, matplotlib

Opombe:

  • Zadnje tri števke študentske številke: 737 (Nemanja Mitric).
  • Poljubno število: 360.
  • Število poskusov: 1.000.000.

Pripomočkovne funkcije¶

In [1]:
from qiskit import QuantumCircuit, QuantumRegister, ClassicalRegister
from qiskit_aer import AerSimulator
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def simulateCircuit(quantumCircuit, numShots=1000000):
    simulator = AerSimulator()
    job = simulator.run(quantumCircuit, shots=numShots)
    result = job.result()
    counts = result.get_counts()
    
    numbers = np.array([int(key, 2) for key in counts.keys()])
    frequencies = np.array([counts[key] for key in counts.keys()])
    probabilities = frequencies / numShots
    
    return numbers, probabilities

def plotDistribution(numbers, probabilities, title, targetNumbers=None, targetProbabilities=None):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.bar(numbers, probabilities, width=1.0)
    
    if targetNumbers and targetProbabilities:
        colors = ['r', 'g']
        for idx, (num, prob) in enumerate(zip(targetNumbers, targetProbabilities)):
            plt.axvline(x=num, color=colors[idx], linestyle='--', label=f'Target {num} (p={prob})')
            plt.axhline(y=prob, color=colors[idx], linestyle=':', alpha=0.5, label=f'p={prob}')
    else:
        plt.axhline(y=1/256, color='r', linestyle='--', label='Ideal (1/256)')
    
    plt.xlabel('Number')
    plt.ylabel('Probability')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

def plotDistributionWithThickerBar(numbers, probabilities, title, targetNumbers=None, targetProbabilities=None):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
    widths = np.array([10.0 if prob > 0.1 else 0.5 for prob in probabilities])
    
    for i, (num, prob, width) in enumerate(zip(numbers, probabilities, widths)):
        plt.bar(num, prob, width=width, align='center')
    
    if targetNumbers and targetProbabilities:
        colors = ['r', 'g']
        for idx, (num, prob) in enumerate(zip(targetNumbers, targetProbabilities)):
            plt.axvline(x=num, color=colors[idx], linestyle='--', label=f'Target {num} (p={prob})')
            plt.axhline(y=prob, color=colors[idx], linestyle=':', alpha=0.5, label=f'p={prob}')
    else:
        plt.axhline(y=1/256, color='r', linestyle='--', label='Ideal (1/256)')
    
    plt.xlabel('Number')
    plt.ylabel('Probability')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

Part 1: Enakomerni generatorji¶

Hadamardovih vrat¶

  • 8 kubitov, števila od 0 do 255, verjetnost 1/256 ≈ 0,00390625.
  • Hadamardova vrata: H = 1/√2 [[1, 1], [1, -1]].
  • Meritev: Kolapsira v 0 ali 1.
In [2]:
def createHadamardGenerator(numQubits=8):
    qubitRegister = QuantumRegister(numQubits, 'q')
    classicalRegister = ClassicalRegister(numQubits, 'c')
    quantumCircuit = QuantumCircuit(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    
    for qubitIndex in range(numQubits):
        quantumCircuit.h(qubitIndex)
    
    quantumCircuit.measure(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    return quantumCircuit

numQubits = 8
hadamardCircuit = createHadamardGenerator(numQubits)
numbers, probabilities = simulateCircuit(hadamardCircuit)

print("Hadamard Generator Probabilities:")
for num, prob in zip(numbers[0:10], probabilities[0:10]):
    print(f"Number {num}: Probability {prob:.6f}")

plotDistribution(numbers, probabilities, 'Hadamard Generator')

Na osnovi rotacij¶

  • Enako kot zgoraj, z uporabo Ry(π/2).
  • Ry(θ) = [[cos(θ/2), -sin(θ/2)], [sin(θ/2), cos(θ/2)]], θ = π/2.
In [3]:
def createRotationGenerator(numQubits=8):
    qubitRegister = QuantumRegister(numQubits, 'q')
    classicalRegister = ClassicalRegister(numQubits, 'c')
    quantumCircuit = QuantumCircuit(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    
    theta = np.pi / 2
    for qubitIndex in range(numQubits):
        quantumCircuit.ry(theta, qubitIndex)
    
    quantumCircuit.measure(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    return quantumCircuit

numQubits = 8
rotationCircuit = createRotationGenerator(numQubits)
numbers, probabilities = simulateCircuit(rotationCircuit)

print("Rotation Generator Probabilities:")
for num, prob in zip(numbers[0:10], probabilities[0:10]):
    print(f"Number {num}: Probability {prob:.6f}")

plotDistribution(numbers, probabilities, 'Rotation Generator')

Part 2: Pristranski rotacijski generator¶

  • 10 kubitov, generiraj 737 z verjetnostmi p = 0.25, 0.50, 0.75.
  • Druga števila: (1-p)/1023.
In [4]:
def createBiasedGenerator(targetNumber=737, targetProbability=0.5, numQubits=10):
    qubitRegister = QuantumRegister(numQubits, 'q')
    classicalRegister = ClassicalRegister(numQubits, 'c')
    quantumCircuit = QuantumCircuit(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    
    numStates = 2 ** numQubits
    stateVector = np.zeros(numStates, dtype=complex)
    
    stateVector[targetNumber] = np.sqrt(targetProbability)
    remainingProbability = 1 - targetProbability
    numOtherStates = numStates - 1
    amplitudeOther = np.sqrt(remainingProbability / numOtherStates) if numOtherStates > 0 else 0
    
    for i in range(numStates):
        if i != targetNumber:
            stateVector[i] = amplitudeOther
    
    quantumCircuit.initialize(stateVector, qubitRegister)
    quantumCircuit.measure(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    
    return quantumCircuit

targetNumber = 737
probabilitiesToTest = [0.25, 0.50, 0.75]
numQubits = 10

for targetProbability in probabilitiesToTest:
    biasedCircuit = createBiasedGenerator(targetNumber, targetProbability, numQubits)
    numbers, probabilities = simulateCircuit(biasedCircuit)
    
    nonTargetProbability = (1 - targetProbability) / (2**numQubits - 1)
    print(f"\nBiased Generator (p={targetProbability} for {targetNumber}):")
    print(f"Expected probability for non-target numbers: {nonTargetProbability:.9f}")

    for num, prob in zip(numbers[0:10], probabilities[0:10]):
        print(f"Probability {prob:.6f} for Number {num}")
    
    plotDistribution(numbers, probabilities, f'Biased Generator (p={targetProbability})',
                     targetNumbers=[targetNumber], targetProbabilities=[targetProbability])
    plotDistributionWithThickerBar(numbers, probabilities, f'Biased Generator (Variable Bars) (p={targetProbability})',
                                    targetNumbers=[targetNumber], targetProbabilities=[targetProbability])

Part 2 Vprašanja¶

  1. Kaj ste morali spremeniti v algoritmu, da ste dosegli poljubno verjetnost generiranja naključnih števil?

    • Nastavi amplitudo √p za |737⟩, √((1-p)/1023) za ostale z uporabo "initialize" (ki uporablja rotacijske vrate).

  2. Ali bi lahko zgoraj navedene poljubne verjetnosti (0,25, 0,50 in 0,75), dosegli s pomočjo Hadamardovih vrat?

    • Ne. Hadamardova vrata dajejo enake verjetnosti (1/1024 za 10 kubitov). Rotacijska vrata prilagajajo amplitude za neenake verjetnosti.

  3. S kakšno verjetnostjo se v vašem generatorju generirajo ostala števila (poleg tistega, ki ga določajo zadnje tri cifre vaše vpisne številke)?

    • p = 0.25: 0.75/1023 ≈ 0.000733
    • p = 0.50: 0.50/1023 ≈ 0.000489
    • p = 0.75: 0.25/1023 ≈ 0.000244

def createStatevectorGenerator(firstNumber=737, firstProbability=0.6,
                              secondNumber=360, secondProbability=0.3, numQubits=10):
    qubitRegister = QuantumRegister(numQubits, 'q')
    classicalRegister = ClassicalRegister(numQubits, 'c')
    quantumCircuit = QuantumCircuit(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    
    numStates = 2 ** numQubits
    stateVector = np.zeros(numStates, dtype=complex)
    
    stateVector[firstNumber] = np.sqrt(firstProbability)
    stateVector[secondNumber] = np.sqrt(secondProbability)
    remainingProbability = 1 - firstProbability - secondProbability
    numOtherStates = numStates - 2
    amplitudeOther = np.sqrt(remainingProbability / numOtherStates) if numOtherStates > 0 else 0
    
    for i in range(numStates):
        if i not in [firstNumber, secondNumber]:
            stateVector[i] = amplitudeOther
    
    quantumCircuit.initialize(stateVector, qubitRegister)
    quantumCircuit.measure(qubitRegister, classicalRegister)
    
    return quantumCircuit

firstNumber = 737
firstProbability = 0.6
secondNumber = 360
secondProbability = 0.3
numQubits = 10

statevectorCircuit = createStatevectorGenerator(firstNumber, firstProbability,
                                               secondNumber, secondProbability, numQubits)
numbers, probabilities = simulateCircuit(statevectorCircuit)

print(f"\nStatevector Generator (p={firstProbability} for {firstNumber}, p={secondProbability} for {secondNumber}):")
for num, prob in zip(numbers[0:10], probabilities[0:10]):
    print(f"Probability {prob:.6f} for number {num}")

plotDistribution(numbers, probabilities, 'Statevector Generator',
                 targetNumbers=[firstNumber, secondNumber],
                 targetProbabilities=[firstProbability, secondProbability])
plotDistributionWithThickerBar(numbers, probabilities, 'Statevector Generator (Variable Bars)',
                                 targetNumbers=[firstNumber, secondNumber],
                                 targetProbabilities=[firstProbability, secondProbability])
